node.text:
Chicken 'cordon bleu' is French for Chicken 'blue ribbon', which is potentially confusing. It also has nothing to do with the famous Cordon Bleu cookery school. Despite these mysterious origins, the concept of deep fried, rolled chicken breast with ham and cheese has international appeal (why wouldn't it). We're taking a new slant on this erroneously monikered dish - introducing it to a wonderful, creamy pasta and adding parmesan - sorry Italy!

INGREDIENTS
2 chicken breasts
Plain flour
Beaten eggs
Panko bread crumbs
1 tbsp butter
3 cloves garlic
300ml double cream
200g gruyere
1/2 cup parmesan
200g chopped ham
1 tbsp dijon mustard
Seasoning
500g cooked penne

#winnerwinnerchickendinner #twistedfood #crispychicken #cheese #chickenrecipes #cordonbleu #croquemonsieur #yummy #food #pasta #chefmode #nom

We also hear about his top recommendations for the best Notting Hill Carnival weekend… next year we hope! Head over to @mamasjerk ASAP to sample some of Adrian’s amazing cooking.

Keshia @sakarah_ from @caribe_uk shows us her take on a Trinidadian favourite, Curry Duck, Dhal Puri Roti with a Chadon Beni Chutney. Notting Hill Carnival may be postponed this year but we wanted to bring the flavours and energy of Carnival to you! Bring A Dish explores the food and culture that this iconic event means to the Black British community and to London. Caribbean food is a melting pot of cultures, influences and history. Head down to @popbrixton to check @caribe_uk out.

Chicken 'cordon bleu' is French for Chicken 'blue ribbon', which is potentially confusing. It also has nothing to do with the famous Cordon Bleu cookery school. Despite these mysterious origins, the concept of deep fried, rolled chicken breast with ham and cheese has international appeal (why wouldn't it). We're taking a new slant on this erroneously monikered dish - introducing it to a wonderful, creamy pasta and adding parmesan - sorry Italy!

INGREDIENTS
2 chicken breasts
Plain flour
Beaten eggs
Panko bread crumbs
1 tbsp butter
3 cloves garlic
300ml double cream
200g gruyere
1/2 cup parmesan
200g chopped ham
1 tbsp dijon mustard
Seasoning
500g cooked penne
